He had his desktop PC at his desk, and his laptop charging on a small shelf at the corner of the room. He was on his computer and seemed to either be working on something or playing a game.

"Hey, what's up Case? I wasn't expecting you to stop by, so, sorry about the mess."

“Oh, nothing much. Just the looming boredom over me.” -They chuckled. Case was in what they usually saw them in. They did almost everything in casual clothes, so there wasn’t much difference- “Just thought I’d swing by, really.”
"Alright, I was just working on a new weapon design. If you want to hang out for a bit, feel free." If Case decided to look behind Antoni, they would see some sort of pistol blueprint open on his PC.

"Oh, its something with a bit of a twist to it! More of a pet project than a proper weapon. Instead of firing a normal bullet, it uses compressed air to launch projectiles. The idea is that it would be able to fire capsules full of paint, or whatever other liquid someone decides to fill them with." He would gesture inside and move out of the way, "Feel free to step into my workshop."
“That sounds amazing.” -They smiled at the thought and then went in, nodding to Antoni as a thank you-
He would head back to sit back down at his desk and get back to work. "I'm just finishing up the design so I can start working on a prototype for it."
-Case watched him sit down, then went over with him to watch him work- “Seems legit. How long’s crafting it gonna take?” -He asked, curious-
"This is a relatively simple one. I might have it done later today, maybe tomorrow. It shouldn't take me that long." He seemed to be happy to have someone to talk to while he was working.
“Seems pretty cool. What’s the gun actually called? Does it even have a name?”
"I've generally heard these types of guns called air pistols. Decided I'd try my hand at making one." He would start to smile a bit. "Want to help test it out when I'm done with it?"
“Of course, dude. Seems like it’ll be fun.” -They smiled back, genuinely excited to test it out-

Antoni uploaded the blueprint he had just finished to his agent and moved to his workbench. He went through a bunch of his supplies to find the ones he bought for this project. Considering how quickly he found them, there was clearly kind of organization in his mess workshop.

"The past day has been stressful, to say the least, so it's nice to just hang out for a bit."

“I can agree with that, holy crap dude.” -Case just watched him work quietly, not trying to distract him- “I need a day to just relax after that whole chip ordeal. It felt like a wild goose chase for a bit there.” -They joked to lighten the mood-

He chuckled a bit at their joke. "Yeah, I'm just happy that we made it through that. We definitely ended up in some bad situations a few times, like that virus." He kept working on the weapon as he talked, seeming comfortable enough with his work to hold a conversation at the same time.

“Ah yes, my Cyber STD moment.” -They chuckled a bit as well- “I feel like me almost dying will be a running gag with this team.” -They then admitted- “First it was me being set on fire, then it was the Cyber STD. Life hates me way too much.” -They gently felt over the scar in memory, which probably still had stitches in it so they were careful with it-

"Mhm. Netrunning is dangerous work, that's why I decided against taking it up in the past. Some of the black ice people have come up with are downright cruel." He sounded genuine as he said that. "Luckily, we usually have Pulse around when you get injured, and I can help when viruses mess with your cyberware. Honestly, I'm surprised I haven't gotten hurt too bad so far. Guess I've just been lucky."

“*Thank you.* Finally someone understands instead of rushing me to hack faster.” -They seemed genuinely relieved that Antoni understood- “And also, you’re extremely lucky to have not been hurt. I don’t know how you do it. Also I think Pulse hates me. I’m always rambling to them whenever they’re treating me.” -They shrugged a tad- “Either way, she’s good at her job. That’s what matters, right?”

"Yeah. I don't know how I've managed it either, especially when that drone was trying to machine gun me down." Then he chuckled a little. "And I doubt she hates you, even if she might get annoyed sometimes. But yeah, she's definitely good at her job, and I'm thankful for that."
-Case chuckled a tad as well- “It’s just nice interacting together as a team. Yeah we don’t always see eye to eye but overall I enjoy it.”

"Yeah, I definitely prefer it to working alone. These past 2 jobs with you and the others have probably been the biggest ones I've ever been on!" He sounded excited to be involved in bigger things than normal. He would grab a screwdriver to start getting things bolted into place.
“I agree. It’s so much more fun with people.” -They nodded, still innocently watching him work-
